Matrics have been sitting for five weeks now with the last exam set for next week Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - The Basic Education Department says that matric exams have been going well across the country despite a few service delivery protests which threatened to disrupt writing. Matrics have been sitting for five weeks now, with the last exam set for next week Tuesday. The department’s Troy Martens says: “We ask that all of civil society to really be aware that our examinations are going on. Thankfully, the disruptions haven’t affected matric examinations this year. We’re very pleased with that.” The results will be released by Education Minister Angie Motshekga on 5 January. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)